1
00:00:02,670 --> 00:00:11,450
SPK_1: Welcome everyone. We are at the end of this journey. We are looking at a thing which comes, at least we think comes at the end.

2
00:00:11,730 --> 00:00:22,630
SPK_1: We stopped before in a place where we discovered that to live in an agnostic world, we have to live as if we are immortal.

3
00:00:22,870 --> 00:00:29,890
SPK_1: But there is a real tricky element to it, like accidents happen, like wars and crime and stuff.

4
00:00:29,890 --> 00:00:36,090
SPK_1: And other people, generally speaking, there is this weird problem that other people actually are kind of cause of our death.

5
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:41,310
SPK_1: So how do we square this? Well, there is an easy solution you might have heard.

6
00:00:41,990 --> 00:00:45,350
SPK_1: Peace to strengths. And that's the topic of the final episode.

7
00:00:45,610 --> 00:00:48,310
SPK_1: So that's effectively the summary and the introduction.

8
00:00:48,530 --> 00:00:54,550
SPK_1: And it might cause the most desire to burn me and the steak that usually comes when I express the paradox

9
00:00:54,550 --> 00:00:59,870
SPK_1: hidden behind what seems the most basic and human.

10
00:00:59,890 --> 00:01:08,350
SPK_1: The most humanist and irrevocable claim of modernity is that peace is good and we all must strive for global peace.

11
00:01:08,590 --> 00:01:13,590
SPK_1: And that global peace is something even desirable and that we can achieve it.

12
00:01:13,770 --> 00:01:19,090
SPK_1: And in fact, there is no such thing as big enough sacrifice to achieve such a world peace.

13
00:01:19,430 --> 00:01:26,230
SPK_1: Well, to me, it represents, at least on the level of political philosophy, an ultimate lie of Gnosticism,

14
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:29,650
SPK_1: which unfortunately is very appealing to us.

15
00:01:29,650 --> 00:01:35,190
SPK_1: Precisely because of all of the reasons we discussed before, like, ultimately, are you pro-war?

16
00:01:35,410 --> 00:01:38,510
SPK_1: Like, that's the most easy natural response. Or are you pro-death?

17
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:40,690
SPK_1: This kind of responses can come into play.

18
00:01:40,830 --> 00:01:48,110
SPK_1: Which just says again that we live in a pretty deeply Gnostic civilization and pretty deeply Gnostic world.

19
00:01:48,390 --> 00:01:50,270
SPK_1: So the short answer is no, but.

20
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:52,770
SPK_1: And this but is important.

21
00:01:53,270 --> 00:01:55,090
SPK_1: The but lies in the following way.

22
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:58,350
SPK_1: The peace Gnostic offers is not peace.

23
00:01:58,710 --> 00:01:59,590
SPK_1: Is a simulation.

24
00:01:59,650 --> 00:02:00,190
SPK_1: Is a simulation of peace.

25
00:02:00,590 --> 00:02:02,850
SPK_1: That's why it's not peace, it's peace through strengths.

26
00:02:02,990 --> 00:02:06,530
SPK_1: Because true peace does not come through strengths.

27
00:02:06,770 --> 00:02:07,990
SPK_1: It comes through love.

28
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:10,970
SPK_1: But we cannot do love because love requires trust.

29
00:02:11,290 --> 00:02:13,690
SPK_1: And love is not exactly about reason and knowledge.

30
00:02:14,410 --> 00:02:18,550
SPK_1: And to love somebody in a broken world, ooh, that's tough.

31
00:02:18,790 --> 00:02:20,550
SPK_1: Like, because also people are pretty broken too.

32
00:02:21,270 --> 00:02:25,070
SPK_1: Like, pretty much, how can you love anything which is not perfect?

33
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:28,490
SPK_1: How, even bigger, how anything not perfect

34
00:02:28,490 --> 00:02:30,630
SPK_1: can be loved?

35
00:02:30,870 --> 00:02:31,310
SPK_1: Ooh.

36
00:02:31,490 --> 00:02:32,670
SPK_1: But again, death is bad.

37
00:02:32,830 --> 00:02:34,030
SPK_1: Death is a destruction.

38
00:02:34,190 --> 00:02:38,030
SPK_1: Death and war and violence and murder.

39
00:02:38,270 --> 00:02:42,950
SPK_1: In a Gnostic paradigm, they are enemy for a very particular reason.

40
00:02:43,350 --> 00:02:45,550
SPK_1: Because this destroys the illusion.

41
00:02:46,570 --> 00:02:50,650
SPK_1: And this destroys the illusion not on a schedule which is set up.

42
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:53,690
SPK_1: So it's uncontrollable destruction of illusion.

43
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:58,470
SPK_1: And this is a destruction of illusion which makes a very important thing to the people.

44
00:02:58,490 --> 00:03:00,190
SPK_1: Kind of difficult, honestly.

45
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:02,390
SPK_1: That's the most difficult part to manage.

46
00:03:02,570 --> 00:03:06,670
SPK_1: Because there is a famous saying in Russian that there are no atheists in trenches.

47
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:12,710
SPK_1: So the closed experience of life and death, willingly or unwillingly,

48
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:16,570
SPK_1: moves a man close to the transcendent.

49
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:20,030
SPK_1: The border between visible and invisible, spiritual and bodily,

50
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:23,150
SPK_1: really becomes sin in this moment.

51
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:23,990
SPK_1: Really.

52
00:03:24,230 --> 00:03:27,570
SPK_1: Yes, there are still Gnostic ways of doing it, but honestly,

53
00:03:27,570 --> 00:03:28,810
SPK_1: really hard.

54
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:31,890
SPK_1: Even Drew Berserk is not Gnostic, just in case.

55
00:03:31,990 --> 00:03:35,310
SPK_1: So it can go really down, but it won't even be that Gnostic.

56
00:03:35,530 --> 00:03:36,050
SPK_1: It's a fantasy.

57
00:03:36,650 --> 00:03:38,110
SPK_1: Apocalypse is now a movie.

58
00:03:38,310 --> 00:03:41,970
SPK_1: Basically, this is an example of going deep down in a spiritual world.

59
00:03:42,110 --> 00:03:44,610
SPK_1: But that's exactly way more closer to the honest pagan,

60
00:03:44,790 --> 00:03:46,970
SPK_1: which is also not what Gnostic wants of a man.

61
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:51,870
SPK_1: And often it can actually make you rethink your suffering and move you higher.

62
00:03:52,010 --> 00:03:53,470
SPK_1: Well, uncontrollable.

63
00:03:53,610 --> 00:03:56,470
SPK_1: Again, it's one thing if I move you to the death on my schedule,

64
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,590
SPK_1: on my term.

65
00:03:57,690 --> 00:03:59,650
SPK_1: But there is always this uncontrollable element,

66
00:03:59,790 --> 00:04:02,530
SPK_1: the one you pointed out before, and I hope you will talk again

67
00:04:02,530 --> 00:04:06,930
SPK_1: what is this uncontrollable element of the deepest point of darkness is.

68
00:04:08,070 --> 00:04:10,770
SPK_1: So ideally, you would prevent it.

69
00:04:11,350 --> 00:04:13,690
SPK_1: Ideally, you would need to do it.

70
00:04:13,730 --> 00:04:16,170
SPK_1: You would take this variable from the equation altogether.

71
00:04:16,650 --> 00:04:17,050
SPK_0: Yes.

72
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:19,670
SPK_0: I feel like I want to go all the way back to the beginning,

73
00:04:19,810 --> 00:04:21,450
SPK_0: which is to say a story.

74
00:04:21,710 --> 00:04:23,050
SPK_0: A lie, but a story.

75
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:26,390
SPK_0: That the world was created,

76
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:28,370
SPK_0: and the world is broken.

77
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:31,190
SPK_0: And what we're saying,

78
00:04:31,370 --> 00:04:32,830
SPK_0: and I agree completely,

79
00:04:32,930 --> 00:04:33,970
SPK_0: and this is experiential,

80
00:04:33,970 --> 00:04:37,530
SPK_0: that it's at the moments where you encounter reality,

81
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:40,730
SPK_0: in spite of anything you may prefer,

82
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:43,970
SPK_0: and almost always on the basis of something that is suffering,

83
00:04:45,310 --> 00:04:46,130
SPK_0: that produces suffering,

84
00:04:46,310 --> 00:04:48,450
SPK_0: or grief specifically.

85
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:51,870
SPK_0: The as if fabric cannot be pulled that far.

86
00:04:52,090 --> 00:04:52,610
SPK_1: Yes.

87
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:55,450
SPK_0: And so you are outside the field of the as if fabric.

88
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:57,830
SPK_0: You sometimes will even look around confused,

89
00:04:58,410 --> 00:05:00,650
SPK_0: because you are suddenly simply in reality.

90
00:05:01,810 --> 00:05:03,530
SPK_0: And you notice that you are,

91
00:05:03,650 --> 00:05:06,050
SPK_0: and something qualitatively has happened.

92
00:05:06,190 --> 00:05:06,330
SPK_0: Feels weird.

93
00:05:06,330 --> 00:05:07,110
SPK_0: Yes, something has changed.

94
00:05:07,310 --> 00:05:09,010
SPK_0: You're suddenly in the world.

95
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:09,750
SPK_0: You're in reality.

96
00:05:10,930 --> 00:05:12,950
SPK_0: And the image of the matrix,

97
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:13,810
SPK_0: the move of the matrix,

98
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:17,770
SPK_0: where everybody is ultimately perfectly not alive,

99
00:05:17,970 --> 00:05:21,490
SPK_0: but is always able to pretend that they are in a simulation of life.

100
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:24,450
SPK_0: I think that's what the image was descending upon them

101
00:05:24,450 --> 00:05:26,970
SPK_0: before the Gnostic syndicate got a hold of those two.

102
00:05:27,270 --> 00:05:31,690
SPK_0: So the phrase that I've been using of trading life for mere survival,

103
00:05:32,390 --> 00:05:37,190
SPK_0: and as you say, trading life for mere simulated peace.

104
00:05:37,450 --> 00:05:38,990
SPK_0: And I get it.

105
00:05:39,230 --> 00:05:41,550
SPK_0: Nobody wants to have grief.

106
00:05:41,910 --> 00:05:44,870
SPK_0: Nobody wants to experience the death of the people that they love.

107
00:05:45,410 --> 00:05:48,590
SPK_0: And in fact, this goes all the way back to this notion of cleaning your room.

108
00:05:48,970 --> 00:05:52,950
SPK_0: It is in fact the case that we should put real effort into keeping our children from dying.

109
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:53,730
SPK_1: Yes.

110
00:05:54,450 --> 00:05:55,310
SPK_0: It is in fact the case that we have to.

111
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:56,790
SPK_0: If we don't, they will.

112
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:58,310
SPK_0: They will put themselves in hazard,

113
00:05:58,390 --> 00:05:59,270
SPK_0: and that will be the end of that.

114
00:05:59,570 --> 00:06:04,750
SPK_0: And so that leveraging of the reality of capacity and responsibility

115
00:06:05,350 --> 00:06:07,710
SPK_0: to avoid highly undesirable events

116
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:11,810
SPK_0: simply gets hypertrophied past its natural reality.

117
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:14,470
SPK_0: That grief has a natural role to play.

118
00:06:14,570 --> 00:06:17,290
SPK_0: That's the weirdest and most untasteful thing.

119
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:20,130
SPK_0: That's the thing you bite into that and you don't like it.

120
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:20,890
SPK_0: You want to spit it out.

121
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:23,770
SPK_0: We want to avoid grief at all costs.

122
00:06:23,770 --> 00:06:24,830
SPK_1: Just to hit it.

123
00:06:24,850 --> 00:06:26,990
SPK_1: Because there is a sleight of hand even here.

124
00:06:27,170 --> 00:06:29,290
SPK_1: Not intentionally, and I know you don't mean it,

125
00:06:29,330 --> 00:06:31,270
SPK_1: but in the language there is a sleight of hand.

126
00:06:31,410 --> 00:06:32,230
SPK_1: About grief.

127
00:06:32,570 --> 00:06:37,210
SPK_1: There is a certain context which we need to understand while talking about suffering.

128
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:43,950
SPK_1: And it connects it both theologically and philosophically to two different realities.

129
00:06:44,490 --> 00:06:46,690
SPK_1: One theological, the easiest way is Isaiah.

130
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:48,770
SPK_1: There is no peace for the wicked.

131
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:53,150
SPK_1: Not there is no peace, but that peace is conditional.

132
00:06:54,090 --> 00:06:57,190
SPK_1: Not that there can be a world without suffering,

133
00:06:57,470 --> 00:06:59,150
SPK_1: but it is conditional.

134
00:06:59,530 --> 00:07:00,410
SPK_1: You see where I'm heading?

135
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:04,630
SPK_1: As long as you live in the wages of sin is death.

136
00:07:05,670 --> 00:07:07,730
SPK_1: Or you can say that the wages of action,

137
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:14,430
SPK_1: all causality, all pure causality necessarily leads up to the death,

138
00:07:14,610 --> 00:07:18,290
SPK_1: like the terminal death of the universe, even if you want to go down just the most.

139
00:07:18,450 --> 00:07:21,750
SPK_1: So if you just stay on this level, in this separated world,

140
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:26,950
SPK_1: you should end up in death because it's just where your natural laws of causality is.

141
00:07:27,410 --> 00:07:31,470
SPK_1: So the Gnostic selling point is that can we stay here?

142
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:33,170
SPK_1: Can we continue sinning?

143
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:37,570
SPK_1: Can we continue being wicked, but still have something which looks like peace?

144
00:07:37,810 --> 00:07:38,150
SPK_0: Yes.

145
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:41,410
SPK_1: And suffering is an antidote against this.

146
00:07:41,610 --> 00:07:45,690
SPK_1: Not against peace, not like you need suffering in heaven.

147
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:49,290
SPK_1: Otherwise, I know you don't mean it, but it might have sounded a little bit like...

148
00:07:49,290 --> 00:07:51,210
SPK_0: Actually, you might, by the way.

149
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:53,670
SPK_0: But the word suffering is a very complex word.

150
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:56,510
SPK_1: Yes, but I really want to show out what Gnostic sleight of hand is.

151
00:07:56,610 --> 00:07:59,910
SPK_1: So ultimately it was be wicked and have peace.

152
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:02,670
SPK_1: And unfortunately, this doesn't work.

153
00:08:02,970 --> 00:08:04,950
SPK_0: Nice. Be wicked and have peace.

154
00:08:04,990 --> 00:08:08,450
SPK_0: By the way, if that's just a straightforward marketing slogan, you get a lot of buyers.

155
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:10,310
SPK_0: Pretty much everybody.

156
00:08:10,970 --> 00:08:14,390
SPK_0: Almost everybody would say, okay, good deal, because I can't be...

157
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:14,470
SPK_0: Good deal?

158
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:16,190
SPK_0: Good deal. Yeah, good deal.

159
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:18,110
SPK_0: Wait a minute. Who's the moron here?

160
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:19,610
SPK_0: Yes.

161
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:21,650
SPK_0: Everybody who doesn't buy that deal is the sucker.

162
00:08:21,750 --> 00:08:23,430
SPK_0: Oh, wait, no, that's not how it works.

163
00:08:23,590 --> 00:08:25,330
SPK_0: Because everybody knows two things.

164
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:28,790
SPK_0: They seek peace and they can't not be wicked.

165
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:32,350
SPK_1: Well, they can, but...

166
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:35,830
SPK_0: And Christ offers you peace, but he also offers you a cross.

167
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:37,310
SPK_1: Conditional.

168
00:08:37,790 --> 00:08:40,010
SPK_1: Ultimately, there's a gap of this conditionality.

169
00:08:40,070 --> 00:08:43,970
SPK_1: And if you remember, again, the story of nativity, it is a conditional statement.

170
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:47,890
SPK_1: Glory to the God in the highest and peace on earth among people.

171
00:08:48,650 --> 00:08:48,950
SPK_0: Nice.

172
00:08:49,330 --> 00:08:50,450
SPK_1: It's not separated.

173
00:08:50,450 --> 00:08:50,990
SPK_1: Right.

174
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:53,810
SPK_0: It's not one and then also maybe two.

175
00:08:53,890 --> 00:08:55,330
SPK_0: These two things are together.

176
00:08:55,730 --> 00:08:57,010
SPK_1: It's causally related.

177
00:08:57,290 --> 00:08:58,950
SPK_1: Okay, not religious language.

178
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:06,970
SPK_1: Only if you ordain your causal ladder of attention to the most proper, to the highest, to the realities such which you embody in your whole spirit,

179
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:17,450
SPK_1: then you can effectively overcome the necessity of entropy and through mystery, miracle, love, trust, basically from all of the...

180
00:09:17,450 --> 00:09:18,430
SPK_1: I'm using this as a metaphor.

181
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:19,610
SPK_1: Maybe you will use it in a ritual.

182
00:09:19,610 --> 00:09:21,330
SPK_1: But effectively, you make the quantum jump.

183
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:21,810
SPK_1: Yeah.

184
00:09:21,950 --> 00:09:23,930
SPK_1: You're making the quantum jump of the causality.

185
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:25,310
SPK_0: Well, right.

186
00:09:25,430 --> 00:09:30,010
SPK_0: So the language is funny because it's a religious word, but we just have no other better word.

187
00:09:30,190 --> 00:09:33,250
SPK_0: I will often use the Greek because it's less loaded, but it's faith.

188
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:34,070
SPK_1: Yes.

189
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:34,630
SPK_0: Yeah.

190
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:37,150
SPK_0: And so let me sort of just articulate what I mean by that.

191
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:45,030
SPK_0: Because one, we know that like all things in the Gnostic civilization, the most important things have been very defamed and perverted.

192
00:09:45,650 --> 00:09:47,990
SPK_0: Faith is perhaps foremost amongst them.

193
00:09:47,990 --> 00:09:49,590
SPK_0: If not very much in the top of the list.

194
00:09:49,590 --> 00:09:55,350
SPK_0: So it has nothing to do with something like willing something very, very strongly.

195
00:09:55,690 --> 00:09:55,850
SPK_0: Yeah.

196
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:56,810
SPK_1: Imagining.

197
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:57,450
SPK_1: Not even willing.

198
00:09:57,710 --> 00:09:59,010
SPK_0: Well, I want to do both.

199
00:09:59,090 --> 00:09:59,210
SPK_0: Okay.

200
00:09:59,330 --> 00:10:03,230
SPK_0: It also has nothing to do with imagining something that is not really the case.

201
00:10:03,510 --> 00:10:06,490
SPK_0: It has nothing to do with imagination or a little bit, but very little.

202
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:10,190
SPK_0: And very little to do with the will or more properly, it has to do with a fully integrated self.

203
00:10:10,330 --> 00:10:10,570
SPK_0: Yes.

204
00:10:10,810 --> 00:10:17,130
SPK_0: The whole point is that faith is the faculty of a fully integrated self in relationship with reality, capital R.

205
00:10:17,130 --> 00:10:20,170
SPK_0: And so I oftentimes will use very banal examples.

206
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:26,850
SPK_0: And it's not, you can say, if I pick up this cup, I have faith that the water will not suddenly come splashing on my legs.

207
00:10:27,070 --> 00:10:28,390
SPK_0: And that's a proper use of the term.

208
00:10:28,470 --> 00:10:28,710
SPK_0: Yes.

209
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,690
SPK_0: That's perfectly reasonable use of the term.

210
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:32,810
SPK_0: We just extend that out all the way, right?

211
00:10:32,830 --> 00:10:33,590
SPK_0: Capital F faith.

212
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:39,130
SPK_0: And this goes back to that notion of the Gnostic sleight of hand has to break your faith.

213
00:10:39,450 --> 00:10:44,870
SPK_0: If your faith is established, if you are actually in continuity of contact with reality,

214
00:10:45,830 --> 00:10:51,450
SPK_0: then the glory to God and peace on earth will be a lived reality that you can perceive as being a thing.

215
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:52,250
SPK_1: And self-evident, kind of.

216
00:10:52,410 --> 00:10:53,030
